Retail Sales Dashboard (Tableau)

*Author:* Monisha B.N.  
*Dataset:* sample_retail_sales_dataset.csv (200 rows, synthetic retail sales data)  
*Tool:* Tableau Desktop / Tableau Public  

 ðŸŽ¯ Project Objective
Design and build an *interactive Tableau dashboard* to analyze retail sales and profitability across Regions, Categories, Sub-Categories, and Products.  
The dashboard provides KPIs, monthly sales trends, product-level insights, and interactive features (filters, parameters, actions).

ðŸ“‚ Repository Structure
retail-dashboard/ data/ sample_retail_sales_dataset.csv workbook/ retail_dashboard.twbx ppt/ summary.pptx screenshots/ dashboard_overview.png kpi_cards.png trend.png top_products.png README.md

 ðŸ“Š Key KPIs
- *Total Sales* = SUM([Sales])
- *Total Profit* = SUM([Profit])
- *Profit Margin*
  tableau
  IF SUM([Sales]) = 0 THEN 0
  ELSE SUM([Profit]) / SUM([Sales])
  END

*Average Order Value (AOV)
SUM([Sales]) / COUNTD([Order ID])
Year-over-Year Sales %
(SUM([Sales]) - LOOKUP(SUM([Sales]), -1)) / ABS(LOOKUP(SUM([Sales]), -1))

*Running Sales Total
RUNNING_SUM(SUM([Sales]))

*3-Month Moving Average
WINDOW_AVG(SUM([Sales]), -2, 0)

*Dynamic Measure Selector
IF [Select Measure] = 'Sales' THEN SUM([Sales])
ELSEIF [Select Measure] = 'Profit' THEN SUM([Profit])
ELSE SUM([Quantity])
ENd

ðŸ“ˆ Visualizations in Dashboard
KPI Cards â†’ Sales, Profit, Profit Margin, AOV, YoY%
Monthly Sales Trend (with 3-month moving average)
Sales by Category (bar)
Profit by Sub-Category (bar, margin-colored)
Sales by Region (bar)
Top N Products (parameter-driven)
Sales vs Profit Scatter Plot (bubble size = Quantity)
Monthly Sales Heatmap
Order Detail Table (drill-down)

ðŸ–¥ Dashboard Interactivity
Filters: Region, Category, Sub-Category, Date Range
Parameters: Select Measure (Sales/Profit/Quantity), Top N Products
Actions: Click Category to filter other charts, hover to highlight
Tooltips: Show Sales, Profit, Margin dynamically

ðŸš€ How to Run
1. Open Tableau â†’ File â†’ Open â†’ select workbook/retail_dashboard.twbx.
2. Use filters and parameters on the dashboard to explore insights.
3. To publish online â†’ Server â†’ Tableau Public â†’ Save to Tableau Public.

